WEBVTT

00:57.890 --> 00:59.792
Sugar Creek, how are we doing?

00:59.972 --> 01:00.653
You guys doing all right?

01:01.133 --> 01:01.434
Good.

01:01.854 --> 01:03.195
So good to see you guys.

01:03.496 --> 01:12.305
Whether you're here at our Sugar Lane campus, or you are joining us online, or you are at my home, the Richmond-Rosenberg campus, we want you to know we love you so much.

01:12.365 --> 01:25.618
And on behalf of our lead pastor, Dr. Harman, who is today at our Richmond-Rosenberg campus, I want to welcome you to the service one more time and tell you that we consider it a blessing to get to do life together and study the Word of God together.

01:26.050 --> 01:38.091
Hey, I want to start today by asking you a question, but I must warn you that this question has the potential of bringing back painful memories, but I want you to know there is a reason why I'm asking you to go through this exercise.

01:38.131 --> 01:40.595
So please bear with me as we go through it.

01:40.655 --> 01:42.519
So here is the question.

01:42.559 --> 01:44.743
What is the most painful memory?

01:44.803 --> 01:49.010
What is the most painful situation that you have ever gone through?

01:49.698 --> 01:56.306
The truth is that we live in a broken world and because we do, we face really difficult situations at times.

01:56.578 --> 02:22.298
I can tell you mine is probably the one when my two-year-old daughter at the time was diagnosed with cancer and they told us in an emergency room that they had to remove her kidney because it was covered with cancer and it was about to spread to other organs and then after that surgery that she would have to go through five months of chemotherapy and those five months that the whole time it was just a really difficult time for us.

02:22.338 --> 02:25.202
We really struggle in a lot of different ways.

02:25.538 --> 02:31.370
And again, the truth is that we live in a broken world and because we do, we experience painful situations.

02:31.891 --> 02:34.096
And for some of you, it might be something similar.

02:34.196 --> 02:38.866
Maybe you or a loved one was diagnosed with something really difficult.

02:39.106 --> 02:41.971
Maybe for some of you, it was the death of a loved one.

02:41.991 --> 02:46.819
Maybe for some of you, it was the betrayal of somebody that you trusted and that you love.

02:47.200 --> 02:49.284
Maybe for some of you, it's the rebellion of a child.

02:49.304 --> 02:53.190
Maybe for some of you, it's a financial crisis that you went through.

02:53.591 --> 02:57.077
Again, the truth is that we live in a broken world.

02:57.137 --> 03:02.226
Since sin entered the world, the world has experienced suffering.

03:03.010 --> 03:08.129
And unfortunately, we have to learn how to navigate through suffering.

03:08.169 --> 03:10.477
We have to learn how to live through it.

03:10.537 --> 03:15.154
And today, we are going to learn a little bit more about how we can do that.

03:15.618 --> 03:20.523
Today we're going to continue this sermon series that we have titled, The Church We Choose To Be.

03:20.563 --> 03:27.751
And in this series, we're trying to understand who is it that God has called us to be as individuals, but also collectively as a church.

03:27.771 --> 03:44.850
And in the first sermon of the series, in the first chapter of Revelation, we were reminded of this glorious Christ that is going to come back one day in all of his mind, all of his majesty, all of his glory, all of his holiness, and he is going to establish a kingdom that will last for eternity.

03:45.282 --> 03:51.169
But in chapters two and three of Revelation, we are reminded of the fact that we have to be prepared for that return.

03:51.209 --> 03:55.814
We have to be ready for His coming and we have to be the church that God has called us to be.

03:56.515 --> 04:06.606
And so in chapters two and three, He actually writes seven letters to seven different churches in Asia Minor that needed to change some things so that they could be prepared.

04:06.626 --> 04:13.714
And I believe that God has allowed those letters to be in scriptures so that we also learn how to be the church that He has called us to be.

04:14.210 --> 04:20.607
Last week Pastor Mark walked us to that first letter, the letter that was written to a church in Ephesus.

04:20.667 --> 04:26.482
And he reminded us of the fact that we choose to be a church that is full of passion for God.

04:27.010 --> 04:32.221
Today, we're gonna look at the second letter we find in Revelation chapter two, verses eight through 11.

04:32.662 --> 04:46.450
And we are going to learn that instead of avoiding suffering or trying to run away from it, we can choose to embrace suffering because God can use it for our good and ultimately for His glory.

04:46.978 --> 04:49.804
Now, I'm not saying that you go and pursue suffering.

04:49.844 --> 04:51.327
That is not what I'm saying at all.

04:51.547 --> 04:54.734
But what I am saying is that we live in an imperfect world.

04:54.754 --> 04:57.780
And because we do, we cannot always escape suffering.

04:57.940 --> 04:59.563
Suffering will come to our lives.

04:59.904 --> 05:02.930
And so we have to learn how to be prepared for it.

05:03.170 --> 05:15.688
In fact, I believe there might be a time when we experience suffering because of our faith, because of what we believe in Jesus Christ and our convictions, and we will be tempted to drop out or to believe something else.

05:15.768 --> 05:25.042
And so instead, we have to make the decision that suffering can be a part of what God can do for good or use for our good and ultimately for His glory.

05:25.858 --> 05:35.418
I want to introduce you to the church that we are going to be looking at today and we find the introduction to the church in verse 8 right there in Revelation chapter 2.

05:35.478 --> 05:36.320
This is what it says.

05:36.881 --> 05:44.658
And to the angel of the church in Smyrna, the words of the first and the last

05:44.770 --> 05:47.032
who died and came to life.

05:47.113 --> 05:48.494
Let me pause there for a moment.

05:48.514 --> 05:53.299
There are a couple of things that we find here that are important for us to understand the message today.

05:53.780 --> 06:02.049
First, who the letter was addressed to, and it says there clearly that it was addressed to the Christians or to the church in a city called Smyrna.

06:02.209 --> 06:10.898
I'm gonna talk about that in a moment, but also I wanna mention that the letter also tells us who is the main author of the content of the letter.

06:11.074 --> 06:14.378
He says that these are the words of the first and the last.

06:14.418 --> 06:18.603
These are the words of the one who died, but also who came back to life.

06:18.623 --> 06:20.625
So it's clearly talking about Jesus.

06:20.685 --> 06:24.870
These are the words of Jesus to the church in Smyrna.

06:25.370 --> 06:28.674
And I believe again that these words also apply to us.

06:29.155 --> 06:35.602
So let's understand a little bit more about Smyrna so that we can understand how those truths apply to us today.

06:36.194 --> 06:38.857
Smyrna was a city in Asia Minor.

06:39.217 --> 06:41.800
It was about 40 miles east of Ephesus.

06:41.860 --> 06:48.686
And it is actually one of the few cities that still stands with the same name and on the same location to this day.

06:49.387 --> 06:54.512
Today, the name of the city is Ismir, which comes from the word Smyrna as well.

06:54.873 --> 06:56.734
And it is in modern day Turkey.

06:57.235 --> 07:01.379
And it is still a beautiful city and it was a beautiful city at the time.

07:01.759 --> 07:04.402
It was actually a very prosperous city.

07:04.578 --> 07:10.986
Historians tell us that there was a street in Smyrna that was paved with gold.

07:11.006 --> 07:13.589
The entire street was totally paved with gold.

07:14.050 --> 07:20.919
Now, I don't know how long a street paved with gold was last in the Houston metropolitan area today.

07:21.339 --> 07:25.985
Probably not long, but apparently it lasted for a long time in Smyrna.

07:26.005 --> 07:33.234
And the reason why this is important is because it gives us the fact that there were also an idolatrous city.

07:33.570 --> 07:40.320
See, this street that was paved with gold actually led to a temple where people worship the Greek God sues.

07:40.680 --> 07:46.949
So we know that there was idolatry in this city, and we also know that there was worship of the Roman emperor.

07:47.910 --> 08:01.970
This was a part of the Roman empire, and a lot of people in the city believed that the Roman emperor was the sent one by God, that he was chosen by God, and the people had to believe in him and bow down to him and worship him.

08:02.850 --> 08:05.514
There were a lot of cities in the Roman Empire who believed this.

08:06.656 --> 08:10.983
In places where this was the case, Christians were heavily persecuted.

08:11.604 --> 08:18.215
Because the Roman Empire saw Christians as a threat to their kingdom, through the Empire.

08:18.316 --> 08:22.002
And so when Christians were around, Romans would persecute them.

08:22.302 --> 08:27.090
And where the Roman Emperor was worshipped, the persecution was even heavier.

08:27.714 --> 08:36.786
So this means that the Christians in Smyrna were being persecuted because of their beliefs, because of what they had believed in Jesus Christ.

08:37.127 --> 08:40.552
And because of that, they desperately needed to hear from God.

08:41.092 --> 08:43.195
They needed to hear a word of hope.

08:43.275 --> 08:48.082
They needed to hear something that would help them keep going in the middle of their persecution.

08:48.578 --> 08:59.392
And so God appeared to John in the Island of Patmos, and he tells him to write this letter so that they would have what they need in the moment that they were going through.

09:00.153 --> 09:11.707
Now, when you read the content of the letter and you're gonna see it a moment, you're gonna quickly realize that they didn't probably receive what they wanted to hear, but they did get what they needed to hear.

09:12.428 --> 09:14.130
Because this is a part of who God is.

09:14.530 --> 09:22.300
God is not necessarily gonna tell us what we want to hear, but God is always out of love going to tell us what we need to hear.

09:22.760 --> 09:26.685
That is the character of our God, because he loves us, he does that for us.

09:27.226 --> 09:32.011
And so I want you to read what he said to them in verses nine through 11 with me.

09:32.031 --> 09:32.892
This is what he says.

09:33.553 --> 09:37.318
I know your tribulation and your poverty, but you're rich.

09:38.179 --> 09:43.986
And the slander of those who say that they are Jews and are not, but are a synagogue of Satan,

09:44.258 --> 09:46.300
Do not fear what you are about to suffer.

09:46.601 --> 09:51.707
Behold, the devil is about to throw some of you into prison that you may be tested.

09:52.148 --> 09:54.530
And for 10 days, you will have tribulation.

09:55.111 --> 09:56.613
Be faithful unto death.

09:56.693 --> 09:58.755
And I will give you the crown of life.

09:59.176 --> 10:03.121
He who has an ear, let him hear what the spear said to the churches.

10:03.561 --> 10:07.506
The one who conquers will not be heard by the second death.

10:08.130 --> 10:09.773
Let me pause there for a moment.

10:09.793 --> 10:19.770
As you can see, basically what the letter says is, I know that you are suffering, but I need you to hold on, buckle up, buckle up because it's about to get worse.

10:19.830 --> 10:20.812
That's what he's saying, right?

10:21.152 --> 10:25.860
He's saying, I know it's difficult right now, but I want you to know it's about to get worse.

10:26.241 --> 10:31.410
Now, this is not a message that you're going to find a stitch in a pillow in somebody's house today.

10:31.682 --> 10:37.992
It is definitely not a message that you're gonna find as you scroll through your feed looking for the inspirational quote of the day.

10:38.473 --> 10:44.703
It is not a message that you often find in pulpits today, but it is a message that is in the scripture.

10:45.003 --> 10:50.872
And in this church, we are faithful to the Word of God and we are faithful to what scripture says from beginning to end.

10:51.133 --> 10:57.042
And so we preach and we proclaim what the Bible says, whether we think it's convenient or whether we like it or not.

10:57.410 --> 11:04.802
And the truth is that we live in a world that is imperfect and because of that, we will face suffering.

11:05.584 --> 11:14.519
And instead of hoping for the best or pretending that everything will be prosperous one day, the best thing that we can do is be prepared for when that suffering comes our way.

11:15.420 --> 11:23.794
In fact, as I mentioned earlier, I believe we will face a day when being a Christian will be absolutely difficult in the country that we live in.

11:24.258 --> 11:35.675
I was having a conversation with a pastor, a wise man, and he was saying, we were talking about this, and he was saying, and the truth is that being a Christian today is a lot more difficult than it was 20 years ago.

11:36.376 --> 11:39.581
And then he said, and the truth is, I believe this is what this pastor said.

11:40.081 --> 11:45.770
He says, I believe being a Christian 20 years from now is going to be more difficult than it is today.

11:46.411 --> 11:47.252
This is a wise man.

11:47.272 --> 11:49.575
You may know him, his name's Dr. Mark Hartman.

11:50.016 --> 11:51.378
You might be familiar with him.

11:51.458 --> 11:53.160
But we were having this conversation.

11:53.180 --> 12:01.851
We're talking about the fact that the church needs to be prepared because it might experience persecution even here in the United States.

12:02.972 --> 12:07.138
And so whether it's a message that we want to hear or not is irrelevant.

12:07.158 --> 12:09.741
The point is that we need to hear this message.

12:09.761 --> 12:12.424
And that's why God allowed it to be in Scripture.

12:13.285 --> 12:17.170
And so today what I wanna do is I wanna walk you through three

12:17.442 --> 12:26.356
truth that I see in this text, in this letter that Jesus needed the church's of Smyrna to hear in the middle of their persecution.

12:26.636 --> 12:36.031
That I believe that if we believe those truths and we practice some decisions within those truths, then we will be able to stand firm, whatever may come our way.

12:36.272 --> 12:40.819
Whatever the suffering that the enemy comes our way, we will be able to stand firm.

12:42.021 --> 12:45.426
The first of those truths is this, because of Christ.

12:45.602 --> 12:49.106
We know God can use our suffering for good.

12:49.794 --> 12:53.677
A few moments ago, across all of our campuses, we celebrated the Lord's Supper.

12:54.058 --> 12:59.082
And in the Lord's Supper, we remember Jesus' suffering through the bread and the crushing of that bread.

12:59.102 --> 13:07.209
But we also remember in that God used that suffering for good, that one day he's going to come back and establish his kingdom, that he resurrected from the dead.

13:07.229 --> 13:12.113
And through that death, he was able to atone for our sins so that we could be forgiven.

13:12.454 --> 13:19.780
So because of Christ and his life and who he is and how he lived and what he experienced, we can know that God has the power to use

13:19.760 --> 13:25.629
our suffering for something good in our lives and more importantly, ultimately, for His glory.

13:26.591 --> 13:28.774
We have to understand something.

13:28.894 --> 13:33.541
I am not saying that God is the one that brings suffering to our lives.

13:33.601 --> 13:34.563
That is not the case.

13:34.843 --> 13:40.272
The Bible makes it clear from the very beginning that God is not the source of our suffering.

13:40.552 --> 13:41.874
The enemy is

13:42.370 --> 13:57.805
From the very beginning in the book of Genesis, we see that God created this perfect world, but there is an enemy that came to try to destroy this perfect relationship that God had with his creation, and to try to stop everything that God wanted to do for humanity.

13:58.886 --> 14:05.033
And so from the moment sin entered the world, because of Satan, suffering has entered the world.

14:05.313 --> 14:10.578
And as long as we are in this world, and before Jesus comes back, we will experience suffering.

14:11.266 --> 14:17.015
Jesus said in John 10, 10 that the enemy has come to steal, to kill, and to destroy.

14:17.516 --> 14:29.694
In Ephesians chapter six, the apostle Paul teaches us that the word that we gauge is not against flesh and blood, but there is a spiritual enemy who's trying to destroy us, who's trying to harm us.

14:30.375 --> 14:34.962
And this is what the Christians in Smyrna were experiencing.

14:35.842 --> 14:38.145
God says to them, I know your tribulation.

14:38.625 --> 14:39.546
I know your poverty.

14:39.786 --> 14:41.768
I know the slander that you are going through.

14:41.949 --> 14:47.775
There are some people who are saying to that they are Jews, but they're really more like a synagogue of Satan is what he says.

14:47.795 --> 14:50.938
This is not saying that Jewish people are of Satan and what he's saying.

14:50.958 --> 14:57.305
And in that moment, in that specific situation, those Jewish people were being used to persecute the church.

14:57.486 --> 14:59.588
And so they were an instrument of Satan.

14:59.868 --> 15:05.234
He was saying that the source of the evil of the suffering is Satan.

15:05.730 --> 15:10.260
That's why he says later that in the future, they were going to experience more persecution.

15:10.300 --> 15:12.987
He says, you will be thrown in jail for 10 days.

15:13.047 --> 15:13.909
And he says, by who?

15:14.250 --> 15:14.971
By the devil.

15:15.332 --> 15:18.299
Both Satan and the devil are the exact same person.

15:18.580 --> 15:24.914
It's the exact same enemy that has been trying to stop God's plan for humanity from the very beginning.

15:25.602 --> 15:31.750
and we have to understand that He is real, and He's trying to destroy what God wants to do for us.

15:32.030 --> 15:37.477
And as we understand who He is and how He works, then we will be able to stand His attacks.

15:37.997 --> 15:45.266
Look at what Peter taught to Christians who were being persecuted in 1 Peter chapter 5, verses 8 through 10.

15:45.286 --> 15:48.570
He says this, be sober-minded, be watchful.

15:48.971 --> 15:54.738
Your adversary, the devil, proves around like a roaring lion seeking someone to devour.

15:55.010 --> 16:01.805
Resist him firm in your faith, knowing that the same kind of sufferings are being experienced by your brotherhood throughout the world.

16:02.366 --> 16:15.314
And after you have suffered a little while, the God of all grace who has called you to his eternal glory in Christ will himself restore, confirm, strengthen, and establish you.

16:15.618 --> 16:17.481
You see that he says there is an enemy.

16:17.521 --> 16:21.267
He's like a roaring lion looking for people to devour.

16:21.287 --> 16:36.530
But if you stand firm, if you resist him, you will see God, the God who called you to an eternal glory, use the attacks that that enemy brings upon you to restore you and to help you grow and to strengthen you and to confirm you and to establish you.

16:36.850 --> 16:42.699
God has the power to use what the enemy means for evil and transform it into something good.

16:43.380 --> 16:44.562
The Apostle James

16:44.610 --> 16:46.233
taught something very similar.

16:46.273 --> 16:49.359
Look at what he says in James chapter one verses two to four.

16:49.880 --> 16:53.447
Can it all joy my brothers when you meet trials of various kinds?

16:53.988 --> 16:58.116
For you know that the testing of your faith produces steadfastness.

16:58.937 --> 17:05.490
And let steadfastness have its full effect that you may be perfect and complete lacking in nothing.

17:05.826 --> 17:18.930
You see that he's saying, when you go through trials, when you go through testing, know that God can use that to help you develop, to help you grow, to help you mature, to help you be the believer that he created you to be.

17:19.491 --> 17:26.443
He says that enemy in that letter to Revelation, he's gonna throw you in jail, but this is just for you to be tested.

17:27.646 --> 17:30.130
And we don't like tests, they're scary.

17:30.402 --> 17:35.488
But at the same time, when we prepare well for a test, then we can grow and we can learn.

17:35.528 --> 17:37.090
That is the purpose of a test.

17:37.550 --> 17:47.982
And so while God doesn't necessarily bring the testing to us or the suffering to our lives, God has the power to use it for our good and to help us grow and to help us mature.

17:48.643 --> 17:50.805
But you have to believe that God has that power.

17:51.026 --> 17:54.930
You can look at the gospel and what God did with Christ and believe that.

17:55.458 --> 18:07.258
See, in your suffering, you can choose to believe that God can transform what the enemy means for you into something good for you and for the good of other people around you.

18:08.159 --> 18:11.926
Now, this is one of those things that it's a lot easier said than done, right?

18:11.966 --> 18:21.682
We can kind of believe that in our heads, but when suffering comes our way, when the difficulty comes, it is hard to believe it and it is hard to remember it and it is hard to stand firm.

18:21.922 --> 18:27.589
And part of the reason why it is hard to stand firm is because we feel like our world is falling apart.

18:27.689 --> 18:30.853
It feels like everything is crumbling right before our eyes.

18:31.755 --> 18:42.408
It leads me to the second truth that we need to learn today is that it's through Christ, God gives us what we need to stand firm in our suffering.

18:42.428 --> 18:50.098
Since suffering has the ability of reminding us of the fact that we are not as in control as we think we are.

18:50.562 --> 19:00.531
When we go through suffering, whether it's financial or health or emotional, we are reminded of the fact that we are not as in control of our bodies as we think we are.

19:00.591 --> 19:03.633
We are not as in control of our finances as we think we are.

19:03.653 --> 19:08.337
We are not as in control of our emotions of other people's actions as we think we are.

19:08.578 --> 19:10.319
So that's why it feels shaky.

19:10.419 --> 19:12.581
It feels like everything is out of control.

19:12.861 --> 19:20.548
But I want to submit to you today that while suffering has the ability to remind you that you are not in control, suffering also has the ability

19:20.528 --> 19:26.258
to remind you that God is in control and that is actually a good thing for us.

19:26.754 --> 19:33.122
When you see the letter here that he sent to the Christians in Smyrna, he says, I know your tribulation.

19:33.503 --> 19:34.844
I know of this lander.

19:35.004 --> 19:41.032
I know of the poverty, meaning I am fully aware of it and I am present in the middle of it.

19:41.052 --> 19:45.358
But you have to remember again that he has a plan and he can use it for, it's good.

19:45.378 --> 19:48.181
He is not unaware of your situation.

19:48.442 --> 19:51.986
Whatever it is that you go through God knows about it.

19:52.962 --> 19:56.768
When a doctor told me that my daughter had cancer, I was floored.

19:57.108 --> 19:58.630
I was shocked.

19:58.650 --> 20:00.032
But I guarantee you, God wasn't.

20:00.894 --> 20:02.676
God knew all about it.

20:02.696 --> 20:08.265
And you might have been surprised by your situation, but I want you to know God was not surprised by your situation.

20:08.625 --> 20:11.790
He knows about your suffering and about your tribulation.

20:12.090 --> 20:17.338
Not only does he know what you're going through right now, he also knows what you will go through in the future.

20:17.659 --> 20:21.084
He says to that church, hey, I want you to be prepared.

20:21.344 --> 20:22.706
Do not be afraid.

20:22.754 --> 20:24.336
There is more suffering coming.

20:24.436 --> 20:26.419
He was fully aware of the future.

20:26.699 --> 20:34.048
He was reminding them that he was present in the past, that he was there in the present, but that also he will be present in the future.

20:34.328 --> 20:38.534
And he knows everything that's happening and nothing scapes his power.

20:39.315 --> 20:45.022
We might not be in control, but that is actually a good thing because we can be reminded that God is in control.

20:45.883 --> 20:49.568
See, when we go through suffering, we tend to respond in one of three ways.

20:50.168 --> 20:51.570
Some people fight,

20:51.746 --> 20:55.391
That means that you try to solve the problem in your own way as much as you can.

20:55.871 --> 20:56.712
So people flight.

20:57.053 --> 20:59.516
That means you can't handle the pressure, so you run away.

21:00.057 --> 21:00.878
And so people freeze.

21:01.298 --> 21:06.324
That means you have no idea what to do, so you can kind of stare at the situation and do nothing.

21:06.845 --> 21:08.747
That's how we typically respond.

21:08.768 --> 21:14.895
But what God wants us to understand is that there is a force and a better way to respond to our suffering.

21:15.256 --> 21:20.242
And that is not neither fight or flight or freeze, but rather with faith.

21:20.802 --> 21:25.508
face in the one that is in control of our lives.

21:25.528 --> 21:31.697
And if we learn how to face our situations with faith, then we will be able to stand strong.

21:32.197 --> 21:37.685
We will be able to risk it and we will be able to grow and become the person that God created us to be.

21:38.526 --> 21:47.959
See, God can use your suffering to change you from being a fearful warrior into a faithful warrior.

21:47.979 --> 21:50.322
And those are two different things.

21:50.530 --> 21:58.061
He wants you to mature, He wants you to grow in your faith and He can even use the suffering that you go through to help you get there.

21:59.763 --> 22:09.938
In fact, when you see Christ's life and how He lived and you read Scripture, you realize that He gives us what we need to stand firm in our suffering.

22:10.434 --> 22:12.237
He gives us everything that we need.

22:12.277 --> 22:21.531
So I wanna walk you through four choices that you and I can make so that we can believe that we can stand firm in the middle of our suffering.

22:21.992 --> 22:24.416
Now, these four choices are not just for suffering.

22:24.496 --> 22:31.767
In fact, I would encourage you to make these choices every single day of your life because they will help you in any other situation as well.

22:32.148 --> 22:35.994
But because we're talking about suffering today, I'm gonna apply to suffering today.

22:36.635 --> 22:38.738
So here's the first one, in your suffering,

22:38.850 --> 22:41.257
choose to embrace your identity in Christ.

22:42.119 --> 22:47.814
Part of the reason why it feels like the world is crumbling before us is because we forget who we are.

22:48.597 --> 22:50.221
We forget who we belong to.

22:50.522 --> 22:54.994
We forget our true identity as children of the Almighty God.

22:56.002 --> 23:00.066
When I was about eight years old, I remember I was trying to learn how to play basketball.

23:00.226 --> 23:01.787
As you can see, I didn't get too far with that.

23:02.187 --> 23:04.970
But I was trying to learn how to play basketball.

23:05.070 --> 23:06.851
And I lived in an apartment complex.

23:06.871 --> 23:09.354
There was a common basketball court there.

23:09.414 --> 23:10.775
And I was trying to shoot hoops there.

23:11.315 --> 23:13.697
And there were some bigger teenage boys playing full court.

23:13.737 --> 23:17.020
And what I was doing is when they were going on that side of the court, I would go on play.

23:17.040 --> 23:20.403
And when they were coming, I would pull my ball and kind of get out of the way for them.

23:20.423 --> 23:23.326
But there was a moment when I didn't make it out in time.

23:23.366 --> 23:25.988
And this one bigger teenage boy got really mad

23:25.968 --> 23:35.500
the fact that I was in his way and he kicked my basketball as far as he could into a field that was on the other side of the fence with really tall grass and it was dark outside.

23:36.562 --> 23:37.623
I was, I mean, I was eight.

23:38.043 --> 23:38.584
He was bigger.

23:38.604 --> 23:39.706
There were a whole bunch of them.

23:39.786 --> 23:40.587
I was by myself.

23:40.947 --> 23:41.628
I was terrified.

23:42.469 --> 23:43.050
I was scared.

23:43.591 --> 23:45.513
And so all I could do was go home and cry.

23:46.434 --> 23:47.776
And I got to my house.

23:47.836 --> 23:51.040
I was crying and my dad was there and he said, what happened?

23:51.060 --> 23:55.666
I told him what had happened and he went into his room, grab a flashlight, put some shoes on and he said, let's go.

23:56.034 --> 23:59.620
You know, he had a flashlight in his hand and thinking, okay, we're going to go to that field.

23:59.640 --> 24:01.884
Even though it's dark, we're going to find that basketball.

24:02.225 --> 24:02.786
But we didn't.

24:02.846 --> 24:06.031
We went straight to the basketball court and he looked at me and he said, which one was it?

24:09.878 --> 24:14.546
And I, with all fear and trembling, went that one over there.

24:15.586 --> 24:17.389
And my dad walked up straight to that boy.

24:17.450 --> 24:20.295
He did not say where all he did was hand him the flashlight.

24:20.375 --> 24:22.519
And that boy knew exactly what that meant.

24:22.780 --> 24:26.367
And he immediately jumped over the fence and went over to look for my ball.

24:27.068 --> 24:34.162
And the whole time he was looking for my ball, I was standing there with my dad next to me and going, OK, who's messing with me now?

24:34.370 --> 24:35.795
It was completely different.

24:35.835 --> 24:36.056
Why?

24:36.136 --> 24:38.324
Because my dad was right there next to me.

24:38.505 --> 24:40.191
I remember who I was.

24:40.512 --> 24:45.168
And I want you to know what John says about you and me who have believed in Jesus Christ.

24:45.188 --> 24:46.132
This is what he says.

24:46.172 --> 24:46.834
Listen.

24:46.978 --> 24:54.745
But to all who receive his name, who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God.

24:55.085 --> 24:58.128
If you have Jesus Christ in your life, that is your identity.

24:58.368 --> 25:00.390
You are a child of the Almighty God.

25:00.610 --> 25:02.712
You are a child of the living God.

25:02.912 --> 25:05.854
You are a child of the one who created the universe.

25:06.075 --> 25:16.964
So when you are going through suffering, instead of being worried and trying to figure out things out on your own, you remember your identity, and that will help you remain standing firm.

25:16.944 --> 25:17.705
in your situation.

25:19.327 --> 25:21.029
Remember who you are in Christ.

25:22.191 --> 25:32.425
There is a second choice that you can make here, and that is, in your suffering, choose to pray to the one who can do something about it, to the one who has power over your situation.

25:33.166 --> 25:35.008
See, when you and I go through suffering, what do we do?

25:35.028 --> 25:35.509
We worry.

25:36.070 --> 25:45.362
We get anxious, and we start thinking about it, and our mind is filled with all these thoughts, and our heart is filled with all these emotions, and we don't get anywhere.

25:45.986 --> 26:14.226
Oh, and you see what Paul said to the Philippians in Philippians chapter four, Philippians chapter four, verses six through seven, it says this, do not be anxious about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication, with thanksgiving, let your request be made known to God, and the peace of God which surpasses all understanding will guard your heart and your mind in Christ Jesus.

26:14.626 --> 26:19.351
He says, do not be anxious, instead bring everything in prayer to God.

26:19.711 --> 26:21.933
And he doesn't say he's gonna make you prosperous.

26:22.073 --> 26:30.081
It doesn't say he's gonna solve the problem the way you want it to, but he does say that he will give you a peace that will surpass all understanding.

26:30.101 --> 26:35.006
Then in the middle of the suffering, he will remind you that he is in control and that he can do something good with it.

26:35.306 --> 26:43.794
And he will guard your mind of all those intrusive thoughts that you have, and he will protect your heart from all the emotions that you are feeling.

26:44.098 --> 26:49.987
Instead of worrying and being anxious, we can bring our needs to the one who can do something about it.

26:51.029 --> 26:57.079
There's a third choice that you can make here, and that is in your suffering, choose to rely on the word of God.

26:57.139 --> 27:04.370
The Bible teaches that we are not to rely or lean on our own wisdom, but rather in the wisdom that comes from God.

27:05.986 --> 27:18.143
And we have this amazing book that was inspired by God so that we could know Him and so that we understand His plan for us and so that we could be familiar with Him and so that we could be transforming to the person that God created us to be.

27:18.423 --> 27:26.855
So every day, make the choice that you are going to rely on the Word of God and when suffering comes your way, you will be able to stand because the Word of God is rooted in your brain.

27:27.876 --> 27:28.978
Look at what it says in there.

27:29.058 --> 27:45.865
2 Timothy chapter 3 verses 16 through 17, all scripture is breathed out by God and therefore profitable for teaching and for reproof for correction and for training in righteousness that the man of God may be complete equipped for every good work.

27:45.925 --> 27:53.938
The way that we are equipped and completed for everything that God has for us is us spending time in scripture.

27:55.458 --> 27:59.625
There is a fourth choice that you can make here that will help you stand firm in your suffering.

27:59.945 --> 28:05.975
And that is in your suffering, choose to listen to the counsel and the guidance of the Holy Spirit.

28:07.096 --> 28:13.106
When we go through suffering, there's all these thoughts that come to our mind, all these voices, all these people speaking to us.

28:13.607 --> 28:18.194
And the best thing that we can do is listen to the counsel and the guidance of the Holy Spirit of God.

28:19.202 --> 28:28.355
When Jesus knew what's about to die, he told his disciples in John 14 what was about to happen, and that they were also going to suffer.

28:28.455 --> 28:30.137
And obviously, they freaked out.

28:30.718 --> 28:33.642
They got scared about the possibilities of their situation.

28:33.903 --> 28:41.874
And I want you to see what Jesus said to them in John 14, 25 through 27, these things have spoken to you while I'm still with you.

28:42.146 --> 28:50.480
But the helper, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, He will teach you all things and bring to your remembrance all that I have said to you.

28:50.941 --> 28:53.425
Peace I live with you, my peace I give to you.

28:53.726 --> 28:56.090
Not as the world gives do I give to you.

28:56.431 --> 29:00.818
Let not your hearts be troubled, neither let them be afraid.

29:01.026 --> 29:07.333
He says to them, yes, I am leaving, but the Father is going to send a helper that will help you in every situation.

29:07.414 --> 29:08.795
He will remind you of my words.

29:08.975 --> 29:10.077
He will counsel you.

29:10.097 --> 29:10.878
He will guide you.

29:11.178 --> 29:13.401
Two chapters later is in John 16.

29:13.661 --> 29:20.870
He said to them, it's actually a good thing that I go away because I can only be here in a specific player, a specific time in this human body.

29:20.890 --> 29:28.018
But when I go away, then the Holy Spirit will come and He will be inside of everyone of you at the same time.

29:28.610 --> 29:32.137
And when you read Scripture, you read that that's exactly what happens.

29:32.157 --> 29:43.838
Jesus ascended into heaven in Acts 1 and in Acts chapter 2, the Holy Spirit came into the life of the believers and they were empowered to live with courage like never before, even face suffering, trusting in God.

29:44.479 --> 29:52.434
And the Bible teaches in Ephesians chapter 1 verse 13 that you and I, when we believe in Jesus Christ, we are sealed with the same Holy Spirit of God.

29:52.578 --> 29:55.663
That means that you and I have the Spirit that was in Jesus.

29:55.683 --> 29:58.227
That means that you and I have the Spirit that was in the apostles.

29:58.427 --> 30:05.118
That means that you and I have the wisdom and the counsel of God accessible and available to us at all times.

30:05.879 --> 30:20.882
And so instead of listening to the emotions, instead of listening to the voices of social media, instead of listening to the voices of the world, instead of listening to what other people are telling us the best thing that we can do is choose to listen to the guidance of the Spirit of God that is in us.

30:21.986 --> 30:25.150
Listen, if we do these things, I guarantee you, we will be able to stand firm.

30:25.591 --> 30:28.775
It won't be easy, but we will be able to stand firm.

30:28.795 --> 30:34.303
And we will be able to stand firm until our suffering ends, because there will be an end.

30:34.864 --> 30:40.351
That is the third point or the third truth that Jesus wanted this church to hear.

30:40.391 --> 30:47.061
That is that in Christ, we have the strength to continue until the end of our suffering.

30:47.922 --> 30:51.026
See, Jesus started a letter saying, I am the first and the last.

30:51.234 --> 30:53.919
He said, I die, but I also came back to life.

30:54.420 --> 30:57.166
Meaning I decide what is the end.

30:57.286 --> 30:58.929
Your suffering is not the end.

30:59.510 --> 31:00.011
I suffer.

31:00.071 --> 31:02.997
He said, I die, but I also resurrected from the dead.

31:03.418 --> 31:09.710
And so he wanted us to understand that there is an end to the suffering that he will bring an end to it.

31:10.031 --> 31:13.778
He says to them, hey, you will be thrown in jail for 10 days.

31:13.922 --> 31:19.318
That means that it was for a specific period of time, that it was not suffering for eternity.

31:19.398 --> 31:21.926
There was an end to their suffering.

31:21.946 --> 31:27.282
And you and I need to be reminded of the fact that our suffering will come to an end.

31:27.458 --> 31:33.124
whether it's in this world or where Jesus comes back, there will be an end to our suffering.

31:33.144 --> 31:42.956
And so the best thing that we can do is fix our eyes on Jesus and walk with Him, trust in Him, and believe that He is our Savior and that He will put an end to our suffering.

31:43.216 --> 31:49.143
And because He will do that, then He is worth us living for Him and even dying for Him.

31:50.124 --> 31:55.570
So you have to make a decision early on in your life, not when suffering comes, but even before that,

31:55.682 --> 32:02.651
that you are going to choose to believe that Jesus Christ is worth living and also dying for.

32:04.293 --> 32:08.178
See, there are things in life that are us worth living and dying for.

32:08.418 --> 32:09.760
My family to me is one of those.

32:11.402 --> 32:18.411
When I went through that cancer with my daughter and she was receiving chemotherapy, I often told God, give it to me, I will take it.

32:19.052 --> 32:19.232
Why?

32:19.332 --> 32:20.614
Because I love her that much.

32:20.754 --> 32:24.018
I would prefer to be the one going through it than watch her go through it.

32:25.346 --> 32:28.470
Jesus is worth living and dying for us.

32:29.832 --> 32:33.998
Listen to what the apostle Paul said to the Christians in Rome.

32:35.320 --> 32:39.867
In case you don't know who the apostle Paul was, he was a Jew who persecuted Christians.

32:39.967 --> 32:44.914
He was a man who tried to do everything he could to eradicate the Christian church.

32:45.666 --> 32:50.218
But then he had an encounter with the resurrected Jesus and he realized Jesus is the Son of God.

32:50.640 --> 32:51.743
And he is the Savior of the world.

32:51.823 --> 32:52.946
His life was changed forever.

32:53.387 --> 32:58.802
He became a Christian and he became the greatest church plan that the church has ever seen.

32:58.978 --> 33:02.261
And so the guy who was persecuting Christian was now being persecuted.

33:02.521 --> 33:04.463
And he often was arrested and persecuted.

33:04.763 --> 33:06.084
And you would think, why?

33:06.344 --> 33:08.306
Why was he willing to go through this?

33:08.366 --> 33:19.856
Look at what he said to the Romans in Romans 8, 18, for I consider that the sufferings of this present time are not worth comparing with the glory that is to be revealed to us.

33:20.176 --> 33:22.939
He said, I know that there is something greater coming.

33:22.959 --> 33:28.964
I have enough to believe that one day Jesus is going to come back in all of his mind, in all of his glory, and what

33:28.944 --> 33:37.935
Whatever I go through in this earth is nothing compared to what I will see one day when I see my Savior Jesus Christ.

33:38.916 --> 33:51.090
And you and I have to make that kind of decisions in our life, not with suffering calm, but now we have to choose to believe that Jesus is truly who he says here.

33:51.522 --> 34:00.914
in your suffering choose to believe the gospel because in the gospel you have what you need to keep going forward until the end.

34:02.018 --> 34:02.919
What is the gospel?

34:02.979 --> 34:06.522
It's a message that says that Jesus came to do for us what we could not do for ourselves.

34:06.802 --> 34:08.404
That he came to suffer.

34:08.704 --> 34:09.424
He was willing.

34:09.444 --> 34:12.747
He didn't have to, but he was willing to embrace suffering.

34:12.787 --> 34:13.048
Why?

34:13.288 --> 34:19.313
Because he believed that God could use that suffering for something good and ultimately for his glory.

34:19.673 --> 34:21.255
And it doesn't mean that it was easy.

34:21.475 --> 34:28.901
Actually, denied before Jesus died on that cross, he was so full of anguish that he was sweating blood.

34:28.961 --> 34:30.483
That was happening in his body.

34:30.803 --> 34:32.004
But he chose to

34:31.984 --> 34:38.030
embrace suffering, a standing firm in believing that God could use him for something good.

34:38.331 --> 34:40.033
He stood firm through prayer.

34:40.113 --> 34:41.154
He came to the Father.

34:41.194 --> 34:47.360
He stood firm remembering who he was and he went to his Father and saying, not my will, but your will be done.

34:47.521 --> 34:55.189
He stood firm by listening to the guidance of the Spirit of God in him instead of resisting the temptation of running away or not going through it.

34:55.209 --> 34:59.313
He went through it because the Spirit reminded me this is going to be for God's glory.

34:59.333 --> 35:01.956
He went through it because he was rooted in the word of

35:01.936 --> 35:06.237
God, and He did die, and He suffered a horrible death.

35:06.880 --> 35:09.714
But the gospel also says that He didn't end there, did He?

35:10.114 --> 35:25.313
Gospel also says that he rose from the dead, that he is alive to dead, and he was exalted to the highest place so that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow in heaven and on earth and under the earth and every tongue will confess that Jesus Christ is the Lord to the glory of God the Father.

35:25.573 --> 35:32.402
And one day he will come back and he will establish that kingdom and he will end all suffering.

35:33.186 --> 35:44.341
If you believe this glorious gospel and you remember this glorious gospel every single day, you will have what you need to stand firm regardless what may come to you.

35:44.361 --> 35:53.693
I remember when I was going through that cancer with my daughter, every Friday we had to go to this children's hospital so that she would receive her chemotherapy.

35:54.154 --> 36:00.562
She had a port right here on her chest underneath her skin and every Friday nurses would pull out this

36:00.738 --> 36:03.362
horrible needles that looked like fishing hooks to me.

36:03.422 --> 36:15.883
They were like big and roundish and very sharp and every Friday they would piece her chest with that needle and every Friday she would cry, terrified because she knew what was coming.

36:16.163 --> 36:25.298
She was only two years old and every Friday she would cry and my job in this whole thing was to hold my poor little daughter through all that suffering.

36:26.338 --> 36:32.448
And the whole time I was holding her, she would look at me straight in the house and say, Papi, no, please, Papi, no, this hurts too much.

36:32.929 --> 36:34.511
Papi, please don't let them do this.

36:34.952 --> 36:41.563
And every matter be frustrated and mad that I had to look at my daughter, watch her go through this and could not do anything about it.

36:42.645 --> 36:46.812
The only thing that I could do was say to her, baby, I need you to trust me.

36:47.934 --> 36:50.578
Please write your hurts right now, but it is for your good.

36:51.010 --> 36:52.712
God is gonna use it for your good.

36:53.012 --> 36:57.939
You resist, you stand firm and you're gonna see that good will come out of it.

36:57.959 --> 36:58.880
You will be fine.

36:58.980 --> 37:00.341
You will be made well.

37:01.363 --> 37:10.935
And by God's grace, after six months of chemotherapy and after a few years of checkup, she was put in remission and she is fine today by God's glory.

37:11.175 --> 37:15.560
And that moment didn't feel like it, but today I can see God used that for good.

37:16.902 --> 37:20.306
And listen, I don't pretend that my circumstances are yours are the same.

37:20.514 --> 37:22.917
I'm not trying to tell you that I have all the answers.

37:23.397 --> 37:27.062
I don't know what you're going through, and I don't know what you're feeling in this moment.

37:27.282 --> 37:30.686
But what I do know for sure is that we live in a broken world.

37:30.706 --> 37:33.269
And because we do, we experience suffering.

37:34.050 --> 37:39.777
And we will probably experience suffering because of our faith one day.

37:40.859 --> 37:46.786
But I also know that this book that we're studying right now, the book of Revelation, started with Jesus saying these words right here.

37:47.487 --> 37:50.290
In Revelation 1, 18, fear not.

37:50.690 --> 37:52.882
I am the first and the last!

37:53.506 --> 37:58.050
And the living one, I die and behold, I am alive forever more.

37:58.310 --> 38:01.333
And I have the keys of death and Hades.

38:01.353 --> 38:12.082
I know that the moment Jesus Christ, He paid for all of our sin and the moments that He resurrected from the dead, He demonstrated that there is an end to this world, there is an end to this suffering.

38:12.282 --> 38:14.004
And one day He's going to come back.

38:14.244 --> 38:18.508
And even if we suffer today, when He comes back, He's gonna wipe away every tear.

38:18.848 --> 38:21.470
And there is not going to be any more suffering.

38:21.610 --> 38:23.492
There is not going to be any more anxiety.

38:23.472 --> 38:34.083
any more depression, any more divorce, any more cancer, any more financial stress, any more of rebellion, any more of divorce, any more of the painful situations that we work through.

38:34.403 --> 38:42.852
It is only going to be the glory of our King Jesus forever and ever and everything will be made perfect one day.

38:43.553 --> 38:52.082
But the only way that we can experience that kind of assurance and that kind of faith is we are rooted in the gospel of Jesus Christ.

38:53.986 --> 39:08.663
if we choose to believe that if God used the death and burial of His Son Jesus Christ to bring about redemption of humanity, then He can choose our suffering for something good and ultimately for His glory.

39:09.604 --> 39:13.528
And I pray that you made that kind of decision.

39:13.548 --> 39:16.772
Let me pray for us to say, God, we love you.

39:18.454 --> 39:22.098
We are thankful for your Son Jesus who was willing to go through

39:22.626 --> 39:27.771
the most horrible and unfair kind of suffering.

39:27.791 --> 39:31.094
But he went through it knowing that you could use it for good, and you did God.

39:31.975 --> 39:36.899
You used it for our redemption, for our salvation, and to give us hope and our future.

39:38.541 --> 39:47.990
And so God, I pray that we choose to be a church that, standing firm of that, on that gospel, then we choose to embrace suffering if it comes our way.

39:49.171 --> 39:52.594
Because we believe that you can use it for our good, and ultimately,

39:52.994 --> 39:53.675
for your glory.

39:54.917 --> 40:08.980
God, we pray that even if suffering comes our way, we choose to be a church that stands firm in the gospel of Jesus Christ and your word and continues to proclaim salvation through faith in Jesus Christ.

40:10.122 --> 40:13.007
Pray this in the mighty name of your Son, Jesus Christ.

40:13.828 --> 40:14.108
Amen.

40:14.709 --> 40:15.090
Amen.

